story: James and Grace were best friends. One day, they went to the market to buy some fruit. James had a few silver coins in his pocket to pay for the apples. Grace picked out the reddest apples she could find. When it was time to pay, James reached into his pocket but realized one coin was missing. "James forgot a silver coin," Grace said, counting the money. James looked around but couldn’t find it. Grace smiled and said, "It’s okay, we can share my coins." James felt happy to have such a kind friend. They bought the apples and walked home together. James promised to be more careful next time. Grace laughed and said, "Just don’t forget the apples!" They both enjoyed the sweet fruit and their fun day. The lost coin didn’t matter because their friendship was worth more.

Silver, of course! James and Grace are two kindergarteners from our community who love to play outdoors in nature. We met each other several years ago, as we live only 1/2 mile away from one another! One day James got an itch and had to scratch it. “Oh no,” we said out loud as my first instinct was to try to stop it by grabbing it and scratching again, but instead I grabbed the bottom of his feet and ran towards the road in search of a large trash container! As I headed to our next meeting, Grace thought, “Wow! This is why I like meeting new people. We got there really quick with lots of practice and a great help along the way!” The following morning we did it all over again because we love each other so much that we feel like family already :) Our 4 year old niece has started calling her ‘James’ because of how similar we are in both personality and interests. James was a bit self-conscious of her lack of experience, “but this is a special place for me,” he thought. “I’m here to meet people who look like me” We both enjoyed the outdoorsy way with all of our friends there to join! When they finally met we all laughed and giggled and then said, “James and Grace, we’ve always wanted to meet one another!” So today it’s a twofer, because of our first meeting James said that it was just perfect for the both of us because not only did he want to help with this project but he also really loved meeting up together to talk about our personalities and interests. We’ve made this an ongoing series, each with their own theme (from left): 2) 1) & 3)
